Posted 13 hours ago

Build a Scheduling Web App

  • Hourly
  • Intermediate
  • Est. time: 1 to 3 months, Less than 30 hrs/week

This project is to develop a scheduling web app. This scheduling app will function differently, and have different features than typical scheduling apps like Calendly. I am NOT looking for a Calendly clone. So please read these project details carefully. This scheduling app is for professionals that meet with clients in their apartments, homes, hotels, office, or other locations. Here is an overview of how the web app should function, and the features it should have: Calendar Syncing: Provide the option to sync with their calendar service, but don't require it. Make this a setting that the Admin can turn on. For example, calendar syncing is OFF by default, but the admin can turn it on for their agency if they want. Registration: The person that completes the registration is an Admin. Here are the required fields needed on the registration form: First Name Last Name Email Role Phone Number Agency Name Agency Address Password. Use 2 factor authentication when creating the account. The registration form should include the option to pay by credit card, or to pay by invoice where payment is due in 30 days. After the admin completes the registration form they should go to a screen where they can invite their staff to create their account that is tied to the agency. When emailing their staff, they need the ability to copy/paste emails so they can send a bulk email if necessary. The staff that are invited should get an email with a link that allows them to create their account tied to the agency. When staff create their account after getting invited, the form should have these fields: First name Last name Email Work Phone Password Use 2 factor authentication when creating the account. Once the staff person creates their account they should land on a screen where they can schedule appointments with clients. This is the landing page staff should land on every time they log into the app. On this same page I would like staff to see the appointments they have scheduled. For example, this page may have a button that says, "Schedule Appointment." After the appointment is scheduled they will see it listed on the page. Login: When a user logs in they should enter their email and password. They also need a "forgot password" option. Use 2 Factor Authentication during the login process. Form to schedule appointments: When the staff person is scheduling an appointment with the client the form should have these fields: - Client First Name - Client last name - Client email (require them to enter it twice to confirm) - Client phone number (require them to enter it twice to confirm) - Appointment Date - Appointment Start time - Appointment End time Location Type: Apartment, House, Hotel, Office, Other. If Other, bring up a text box to enter the type. - Address - Purpose of appointment. Have a dropdown where staff can select the purpose of the appointment. Allow the agency to customize the selections available in their dropdown. After the appointment is scheduled give staff the option to add to their calendars. This should be a link or button where the staff person can add it to their calendar. The app sh ould support all major calendar services like Outlook, Gmail, and Apple. In the Details section of the calendar invite include the location Type and purpose of the appointment. After the appointment is scheduled a notification email and text message should get sent to the client with a link to add it to their calendar. The calendar invite headline should say: "Meeting with Client First Name Client Last Name and Staff First Name Staff Last Name from Agency Name" Clients do NOT get a login to use the app. Clients only get notifications of appointments scheduled with the option to add it to their calendars. In the confirmation email and text message, the client should also get a link that says, "Need to cancel this appointment?" If they click the link it should take them to a page or dialogue box that says, "Are you sure you want to cancel this appointment?" If they click yes, it should send a notification to the staffperson that the appointment has been cancelled. Appointment Reminders 24 hours before the appointment clients should get an email and text message reminding them of the appointment. These reminders should also include the link "Need to cancel this appointment? 1 hour before the appointment clients should get an email and text message reminding them of the appointment. These reminders should also include the link "Need to cancel this appointment? Additional Features Needed: When the appointment starts staff should check in (which means they arrived at the location of the appointment and it is starting). They can check in by clicking a link in the reminder text/email or by clicking a link or button in the app. If they haven't already, at the start time of the appointment staff should get an email and text reminder to check-in for the appointment. (Message: Remember to check in for your appointment!). If they haven't checked in after 10 minutes of the start time send another email and text reminder to check into the appointment (Message: Remember to check in for your appointment!). If the staffperson has not checked in after 15 minutes of the start time, send an email and text message to a "safety notification contact" to notify them that the staff person has not checked into the appointment. Message: "Staff First Name, Staff Last Name has not checked into their appointment with Client First Name, Client Last Name at Address. Staff Phone Number: XXX-XXX-XXXX Staff should also check out of the appointment at the end time. If they haven't already checked out of their appointment, at the end time staff should get an email and text that says, "Remember to check out of your appointment!" And provide a link they can click to check out. If they haven't already, 10 minutes after the end time of the appointment send the staff person another reminder email and text with the message, "Remember to check out of your appointment" and provide a link they can click to check out. If they haven't already checked out after 15 minutes, send an email and text message to a "safety notification contact" to notify them that the staff person has not checked out of the appointment. Message: "Staff First Name, Staff Last Name has not checked out of their appointment with Client First Name, Client Last Name at Address. Staff Phone Number: XXX-XXX-XXXX We also need the ability for a staff person to cancel the appointment. This can be a link or button that when it is cancelled it automatically sends an email and text message to the client notifying them that it was cancelled. We need the ability for staff to notify the system that the appointment is starting late or ending late. For example, maybe the client is showing up late, or they are late due to traffic or weather. This could be a link they can click that says, "Delay the start time of your appointment?" or "Delay the end time of your appointment? Then, when they click on it they can decide by how much, 5 minutes, 10 minutes, 15 minutes, etc. Reporting Dashboard Agency Admins and anyone they give permission to should have access to a detailed reporting dashboard that they can filter by date (and date range), staff person, appointment type, appointment location. They should be able to see: - Total Number of Appointments Scheduled - Purpose of Appointment - % that started on time - % that ended on time - % cancelled - % check in - % check out - % start time delayed - % end time delayed - Number of safety notifications sent - % of appointments where safety notifications were sent Staff should also have access to the reporting dashboard. However, staff can only see data for their specific appointments. This app also needs to be HIPAA Compliant. Roles/Users that need access (a login) to the app, and the permissions that they need: Role #1 - Agency Admin - Create and manage agency account - Pay by credit card or invoice - Manage Notification Preferences and Permissions - Invite staff to create an account - Manage Staff Access (Add staff, Remove staff, Transfer Staff Account to Other People) - Manage staff roles and persmission levels - All appointment scheduling features - Access to Reporting Dashboard Role #2 - Staff - Schedule Appointments - Check into appointments - Check out of appointments - Cancel Appointments - Delay start time of appointments - Delay end time of appointment - See appointments they have scheduled Role #3 Safety Notification Contact This role is notified by email and text when staff has not checked into an appointment or out of an appointment. Note: I have Stripe and Twilio/SendGrid accounts that we can use for payment processing and notifications.
